children.characters: A “card” is a UI design pattern that groups related information in a flexible-size container

children.name: Text
children.characters:
A “card” is a UI design pattern that groups related information in a flexible-size container, most of the time visually resembling a playing card.

There are two types of card available:

Standard Cards 
Media Cards

Standard Cards are containers for most type of content and are used to segment detail on a page.
Examples of use in Pendo:
Dashboard widget
To contain tables
Segment rules

Media Cards are used to display content and actions on a single topic, typically where there is a need to display rich media, together with text and call to actions - Examples of use in Pendo:
Widget selectors
Guide layout selectors

children.characters: Using standard cards in your project

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Cards are flexible to hold any type of content - you can resize them to fit to your screen size.
Cards have 3 seperate content areas: Header, Body and Footer
Card Header consists of 3 slots where you can place your own content built from your local file. There are also a few presets available to use as a starting point - These are our most common design patterns. Presets be modified to your needs, as they are built using the same core card component, you can simply opt to change text in them or go as far as switching out the slot container
Card Body consists of a single slot - switch out the slot instance with a single component you’ve built in your local file.
Card Footer consists of a single slot - switch out the slot instance with a single component you’ve built in your local file.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Collapsible cards are a preset called “🌈 Card Collapsible Preset”

You can switch off the boolean “Body?” to make the card look collapsed
Click into the button states of the “🌈 Collapse Action” component to mimic the interaction in your prorotypes
Use smart animate to create animation between collapsed and expanded states

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Link cards are a preset called “🌈 Card Link Preset”.

This is a common pattern, but you can modify it to your needs - taylor it to your needs, or modify it completely by switching the slot instances as with a standard card.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Link cards are a preset called “🌈 Card Center button Preset”.

This is a less common pattern, however it shows the pattern case of the middle slot in a card header.
